    <abstract>
      <t>This document specifies the use of H3 and LISP for Geolocation Services. Geolocation Services utilize geospatial for: Fresh HDMaps, Intelligent Driving, Cruise and Parking assists. Geospatial utilization is delivered using in-network curation, verification, localization, and brokering of geospatial data using: - EID addressable geospatial tiled-abstraction of road-segments. - EID Interface for detections and uploads to a geospatial-context. - EID Routing-Sharing hazards, blockages, parking, road-inventory. - EID geospatial themed multicast channels to subscribed clients.</t>
